how create virtual environment using Anaconda prompt

##If you are using Anaconda here is the solution. This command lists all the discoverable environments
>>conda info --envs
or 
>>conda env list

##Check if conda is installed in your path.
>>conda -V

## Update the conda environment 
>>conda update conda

step1:Set up the virtual environment
>>conda create -n envname python=x.x anaconda

step2: Activating the virtual environment
>>conda activate envname

step3:Installation of required packages to the virtual environment
>>conda install -n yourenvname package

step4:Deactivating the virtual environment
>>conda deactivate

step5: Deletion of virtual environment
>>conda remove -n envname -all

## install pip in your environment to install other packages
>>conda install pip
